{"TopicId":209905,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"Good HOTAS setup?","CreatedByName":"Cloakedwand72","CreatedById":38144,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-26T18:27:50Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Cloakedwand72","CreatedById":38144,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-26T18:27:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThinking of dipping my toes into the HOTAS would I do t want to spend several hundred on the Winwing or Virpl and Warthog sticks right yet. I\u2019m a intermediate flight simmer I\u2019m thinking of grabbing the X52 Logitech system and Maybe rudder pedals. I\u2019m not interested in yokes as I enjoy flying helicopter\u2019s also, Any recommendations?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlamoVampire","CreatedById":78020,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-26T23:00:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI run logitechs rhino x56 hotas. I would suggest the 56 for flight simming as it has more switches but far more importantly you can split the throttle into dual engine controls. Its a bit more pricy iirc than the 52 but its a solid hotas.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n180009262022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-28T16:14:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224179317\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209905\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221664233238\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278020\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AlamoVampire\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/27/2022 at 1:00 AM, AlamoVampire said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI run logitechs rhino x56 hotas. I would suggest the 56 for flight simming as it has more switches but far more importantly you can split the throttle into dual engine controls. Its a bit more pricy iirc than the 52 but its a solid hotas.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n180009262022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022logitech-g-saitek-x56-rhino-v2-flight-co\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022166.67\u0022 height=\u00221200\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.elkjop.no/image/dv_web_D180001002220674/LTGSFLX56PRV2/logitech-g-saitek-x56-rhino-v2-flight-control-system--pdp_zoom-3000.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd I thought my naga mmo mouse with 12 side buttons had lots of stuff.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nHere you got two d pads on top of the stick, you can twist or pull the stick up and down in addition to the standard movements, the throttle is split and has two wheels for trim or similar.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nThat is pretty wild.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlamoVampire","CreatedById":78020,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-28T23:51:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57801-magnemoe/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257801\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57801-magnemoe/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@magnemoe\u003C/a\u003Eits a fantastic hotas. Multiple springs for options on how stiff the joystick feels and you can customize its led colors plus much more. Its not top tier but fairly close to it \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E185109282022\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cloakedwand72","CreatedById":38144,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-30T05:15:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224180101\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209905\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221664409071\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278020\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AlamoVampire\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/28/2022 at 7:51 PM, AlamoVampire said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57801-magnemoe/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257801\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57801-magnemoe/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@magnemoe\u003C/a\u003Eits a fantastic hotas. Multiple springs for options on how stiff the joystick feels and you can customize its led colors plus much more. Its not top tier but fairly close to it \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022tel:185109282022\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E185109282022\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice might look at that setup! I\u2019ve hear QC issues on Logitech brand but can not afford virpl etc. Also want something with hall sensors.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlamoVampire","CreatedById":78020,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-30T08:13:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/38144-cloakedwand72/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002238144\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/38144-cloakedwand72/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Cloakedwand72\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0ive had mine for a few years now and had no real issues with it. Well aside from deciding what color to set its lights to lol. I went with green. Same color choice on my rig too. Kinda has a Borg glow about it lol. Really is a solid well built setup.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n031309302022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dafni","CreatedById":149636,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-30T10:54:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224180567\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209905\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221664525589\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278020\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AlamoVampire\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, AlamoVampire said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/38144-cloakedwand72/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002238144\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/38144-cloakedwand72/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Cloakedwand72\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0ive had mine for a few years now and had no real issues with it. Well aside from deciding what color to set its lights to lol. I went with green. Same color choice on my rig too. Kinda has a Borg glow about it lol. Really is a solid well built setup.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n031309302022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow are the dead-zones of the stick, if I may ask? I went with the Warthog back in the day for it\u0027s solid feel, but now sometimes I miss the twist stick. This looks like a contender, but I\u0027m a stickler for that solid feel in sticks. So how is the dead center wiggle on this one? If you compare it to other sticks?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMany thanks in advance, appreciate your time and input.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Daf\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cloakedwand72","CreatedById":38144,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-01T03:57:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224180567\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209905\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221664525589\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278020\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AlamoVampire\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 hours ago, AlamoVampire said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/38144-cloakedwand72/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002238144\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/38144-cloakedwand72/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Cloakedwand72\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0ive had mine for a few years now and had no real issues with it. Well aside from deciding what color to set its lights to lol. I went with green. Same color choice on my rig too. Kinda has a Borg glow about it lol. Really is a solid well built setup.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022tel:031309302022\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E031309302022\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurious how do the switches feel? Do they feel plasticy also thinking of the thrustmaster TWCS HOTAS. Also does the X56 have hall sensors?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-10-01T04:01:33Z\u0022 title=\u002210/01/2022 04:01  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 1, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by Cloakedwand72\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cloakedwand72","CreatedById":38144,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-01T04:11:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224179973\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209905\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221664381646\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/28/2022 at 12:14 PM, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.elkjop.no/image/dv_web_D180001002220674/LTGSFLX56PRV2/logitech-g-saitek-x56-rhino-v2-flight-control-system--pdp_zoom-3000.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022logitech-g-saitek-x56-rhino-v2-flight-co\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022166.67\u0022 height=\u00221200\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.elkjop.no/image/dv_web_D180001002220674/LTGSFLX56PRV2/logitech-g-saitek-x56-rhino-v2-flight-control-system--pdp_zoom-3000.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd I thought my naga mmo mouse with 12 side buttons had lots of stuff.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nHere you got two d pads on top of the stick, you can twist or pull the stick up and down in addition to the standard movements, the throttle is split and has two wheels for trim or similar.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nThat is pretty wild.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh I heard lots of mixed things about this set up also\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://youtu.be/2Alj15nyi3o\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://youtu.be/2Alj15nyi3o\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlamoVampire","CreatedById":78020,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-01T04:28:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149636-dafni/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022149636\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149636-dafni/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dafni\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0deadzone wiggle on MY set up with the spring im using isnt too bad, few degrees of slop but I think it has more to do with spring strength. Does not affect performance as far as i can tell. Ive been in some wild dog fights and mach 1\u002B canyon runs in DCS with this stick \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/38144-cloakedwand72/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002238144\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/38144-cloakedwand72/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Cloakedwand72\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0switches feel pretty good for the most part. As to hall sensors im not sure to be honest but id think there are based off a few of the smaller thumb sticks on it, but im not 100% certain\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n232809302022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cloakedwand72","CreatedById":38144,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-01T07:25:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224180894\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209905\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221664598509\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278020\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AlamoVampire\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, AlamoVampire said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149636-dafni/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022149636\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149636-dafni/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dafni\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0deadzone wiggle on MY set up with the spring im using isnt too bad, few degrees of slop but I think it has more to do with spring strength. Does not affect performance as far as i can tell. Ive been in some wild dog fights and mach 1\u002B canyon runs in DCS with this stick \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/38144-cloakedwand72/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002238144\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/38144-cloakedwand72/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Cloakedwand72\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0switches feel pretty good for the most part. As to hall sensors im not sure to be honest but id think there are based off a few of the smaller thumb sticks on it, but im not 100% certain\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022tel:232809302022\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E232809302022\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny stick and throttle with a hall sensor? I\u2019ve been too used with that on my old stick.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlamoVampire","CreatedById":78020,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-01T09:38:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/38144-cloakedwand72/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002238144\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/38144-cloakedwand72/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Cloakedwand72\u003C/a\u003E i just did a quick google:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdjustable Accuracy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe combination of contact-free Hall effect sensors within the 16-bit aileron and elevator axis, and the adjustable spring tensioning system gives X56 an unprecedented level of sensitivity and control at the stick. Four springs of differing tensions are included for an extra layer of customization.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nright now tho logitech says its sold out. Hope this helps \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E043810012022\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}